A lot going on I suppose.
Which is a good thing in summer.
My mind is basically focused on tennis.
I gave up trying to find a job.  It will interfere with tennis camp and all that business.
But yeah, tennis camp started last week.
I've been helping with kid's camp so I can get my camp for free.
I've been coming in early to get extra training with coach.
There's also going to be a team tennis thing.  Coach made me captain of one of the teams.  He volunteered me.  =/
UTSA is doing a team tennis thing as well, so I contacted one of the coordinators and hopefully she'll get back to me.
I just ordered a new racket so I don't have to use my nasty N6 anymore.

I'm looking forward to July.
It sounds really nerdy but my e-friends are coming to the Chi to visit me.
I won't be able to see them the first two days they come, but on Wednesday and Thursday we're going to go to Woodfield and Gameworks.
=]
So I'll be spending a lot of money and gas for those days.
Haha.

I'm going to have to start studying for my ACTS again.
I'm definatly not satisfied with my score.  So the last month of summer, I'll be studying like crazy.
And playing tennis of course.

I want to go to state this year.

asian.
SOMEONE GIVE ME A FUCKING JOB.

I'm going to miss Acen and second day of boy's conference because of Selena's graduation.
This sucks.

Downer's Grove invite.
Five shirts.
Three pants.
Two pairs of socks.
Spent almost all of the tournament on the bus.
The courts were next to a BP so I went there with everyone a lot.
They made fun of the way I sleep.
We got last place.
Some intense matches.
Some bad ones.
There was a lot of wrestling on the bus.
Tyler held back my hands and let people hit me, but I got him so it's chill.
Bumpy bus ride home.
Almost threw up on Tyler.
I hate Sundays.

So cold.  Just spent two hours in 30 degree weather.
Shows how much I love the tennis guys.
Wore my Seigaku pants and all the asians lawled.
Tomorrow, tournament at...I forgot.
But yeah.  High is only 36.
Time to layer.

I really love being manager of boy's tennis.
No drama.
We all just play.
It's so much more fun.
I love being with the guys.

Scattergories!!!
Scattergories...harder than it looks!
Rules: Use the 1st letter of your last name to answer each of the following... They MUST be real places, names, things... NOTHING made up! If you can't think of anything, skip it. Try to use different answers if the person in front of you had the same 1st initial. You CAN'T USE Y0UR NAME for the boy/girl name question.

Your Name: asian Nanthvong.

1. Famous Music Artist: Nine Inch Nails

2. 4 letter word: Nail.

3. Street name: N. Lyle.

4. Color: Navy.

5. Gifts/presents: Necklace.

6. Vehicle: Nissan.

10. Things in a Souvenir Shop: Notebooks

11. Boy Name: Nick

12. Girl Name: Nicole.

13. Movie Title: Night at the Roxbury.

14. Alcoholic drink: Uhhh.

15. Occupations: Ninja.

16. Flowers: ...

17. Celebrities: Nicole Richie Lolz.

18. Magazine: Uhh.

19. US city: New York City.

20. Pro Sports Teams: New York Yankees.  >.>

21. Something Found in a kitchen: Nuts.

22. Reason for Being Late: Not having a ride.

23. Something You Throw Away: Notes.

24. Things You Shout: NIGGER.

25. Cartoon character: Naruto.

Selena came home on Friday.
We had a talk on Saturday while we were finding the emissions test building.
She understood how much I'm getting sick of this place.
And how I want to meet new people.
And I've gotten to a point where I can't tolerate anyone anymore.
She said it's good for me to be like that.
Beucase it makes me appreciate college more.
She said that it's hard to have friends in high school.
And it's even harder to fit in with your clique.
She said it doesn't matter since you find your real friends in college anyway.
It's funny how I thought we were different.
But in a way we're insanely alike.
I've been thinking that after college I'll move out of America.
Probably to South Korea, Japan or Thailand.
I want to start a new life when I grow up.

asian

I hate this place.
I want change.
I want to leave.
I hate everything about this place.
I should have run away in Japan.

FEBUARY 13.
1700.
HOUSE OF BLUES.
KEVIN.  CHLOE.  NICOLE.
DIR EN GREY.
GOING TO BE THE BEST NIGHT EVER.

I just studied four hours worth of algebra, halfway done!
My mom said for every A I get this semester, she'll get me a manga.
YESSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS.
GO ME GO.
I'm on a break BTW.
Waiting for dinner.

I know I shouldn't be happy.
I really shouldn't.
But I can't take this grin off my face.

I started watching Inital D, Im almost done with the First Stage.
Its got me really worked up about cars again.  And I really want to go out there and drive.
Im starting to learn a little about cars as well, so thats always a plus.
I really want a EG-6 or a Sil-Eighty.
I wish I could drift.
Haha.

1. List twenty things you wish you could say to people but can't.

2. Don't say who they are.

3. Never discuss it again.



-Sometimes I feel like we're living completely different lives.  We're not as close as we used to be.  But thank you for putting up with me for so many years.

-You listen to me no matter how ridiculous my reasoning is.  You tell me things in a striaght forward fashion and give me so much advice.  You let me cry and you cheer me up.  I don't think I've ever met a better friend.

-You're one of my favorite people to hang out with.  Even if we do have some differences we always end up thinking the same way.

-You're a great friend and you always let me vent out my frustrations, you're always there when I need you.

-Even though you're so far away I can still talk to you about personal problems.  You try to help me through all my issues and I'm really greatful.

-I have feelings for you.  I wish I didn't but I do.  Sometimes you hurt me, but it's unintentional.  I wish I wasn't such a bother to you.  And no matter how many times I tell myself to forget these feelings for you I won't.  Even though I won't see you after first semester and my feelings may fade, I'll see you again come springtime when the weather is nice, and I'll fall for you all over again.

-Thanks for always cheering me up and talking to me and going wtih me on spontanious trips.  I wish we could be closer.

-We've been drifting away, I barely see you anymore, and when I do it's with someone else.

-You're always there for me, and you tell me the honest truth.  No matter how much it hurts.  You're so far away and you have other people.  I wish I could keep you by me forever sometimes.  I love you so much and I wish I could thank you for everything.

-Even if you are amazingly ridiculous and sometimes short tempered I still love you.  No matter how angry I seem.

-You ignore me, but it's okay.  You're just really tired and I understand that.  I wish you would make more of an effort though.  No matter how much I complain about you I still love you.  Even if you are insanely dramatic.

-I used to have the biggest crush on you and I wanted to get to know you better.  The feelings have faded though but because of my feelings for you back then I'm able to have a better friendship with you.

-Sometimes I wonder how you feel.  I think you're hiding things from others, and most importantly yourself.  I wish you would confide in me more.

-Even if you live in Japan, I LOVE YOU, AND I WANT YOUR PENIS.  PLEASE LET ME HAVE YOUR CHILD.
*cough*  Just kidding.

 

Hmm...how sad, I can't think of enough people.

asian.

Went to Jewel for bell rinigng today.  It was pretty fun.  Goofed off with Dally and made a fair amount of money.  Chloe stopped by.  :)
Then we went to Beef Villa and had lunch.  And Dally was like, "Asian!  Get the straw out for me!  My fingers are too fat!"
I laughed and so did the cashier.  :)
Dropped Dally off and drifted a little on her street.  :D
We almost crashed into a car.
:D
Took the long way home by Kimball and I saw Richard driving in front of me to turn into the gas station.
I honked.
:)
And then I turned on my street and basically drifted alllllll the way down.
It was AMAZING.  And then my car started doing a fishtail and yeah.
Fucking fun as hell.


-asian

Went to Geneva commons today.  Stopped by Forever 21, and Gap.
Didn't find anything though.
Went to Old Navy and got some jeans, and a shirt.
I never realized how much I love long sleave shirts.
Signed up with an Old Navy card.
WHOOT.
:D
I can use it to my hearts content.
(possibly)
Went to Borders and got Prince of Tennis 16.
FWHOOOOOOOOOOOOT.
:D
Went to Kripsy Kreme and got some doughnuts.
My mom kept calling it creamy doughnuts.
Lawl.
Came home, spent an hour trying to figure out why the Simpsons weren't on.
IT'S SATURDAY.
:|
Working on my art project right now.
:)

asian

Fun ride home today!
We were leaving the parking lot and all of a sudden Richard speeds up as we're crossing the street.
And I was gonna yell at him because a bus was REAAAAL close to us.
And then we were on Lyle and he starts breaking and we were laughing so much.
And then he switched it to first gear and did it again and it was jerking around like crazy.
Oh man.
Uber fun.

Went to Algonquin commons.
Went to Dick's and got some AWESOME pants.
I got NIKE pants that are really similar to these pants that I really wanted.
And these HAWT Puma pants that are uber smexy.
Went to Border's and got Bleach 15.  Then went home and yeah.
My dad got a stringer from work and I was gonna have him teach me how.
Go figure HE DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO STRING.
Stupid liar.
So I talked to Richard and he said he would come over and show me.
But something made it really weird for him and he didn't want to come.
And told me to come over instead.
So I met up with him at Kimball, then dropped off my car at his house.
Went to Quiznos and it was closed.
Then we went to Subway and pulled up and saw an indian lady sitting there that worked there.
As we're halfway out of the car she stands up and turns off the open sign.  FIFTEEN minutes before they close!
And we were like, "WTF." And she stood there and watched us until we left.
Ghey.
Yes.
So we went to McDonald's instead and he started ordering food.
"You want anything?"
"No, I'm fine."
"...One chicken sandwhich."
"..."
I punched him in the arm.
Went to his house and met his brother and mom.
He ate for a little and then we realized that my dad didn't bring clamps from work.
So we called Andrew and went to his house to open the garage and everything.
But the code didn't work.  Or it wouldn't open or something.
So we couldn't get the clamps.  Then I called Dally and asked if we could borrow hers, but she couldn't find them.
So we went back to his house and he showed me how to string anyway.
Then my mom called and I had to go home.
And...the end.

Okay I lied.
So when we were driving around Richard kept putting these sex related songs on.
UBER AKWARD.
Like woah.
Like that one Panic at the Disco song.  Wow...
And then after that he put on a really really sexual one on.
*cough*
Kevin said he was throwing himself out there.
I think it was a coeincidence.
And...
The end.

asian
<font size="1">Am I stupid for crying this much?</font>

So today I...took a nap.
Read.
Went to Walmart.
Went to the courts.
But no one was there
i was really energetic so I did some suicides.
i went to the library and got some more manga.
Then went back to the courts.
Then came home.
Showered.
Did 15 sets of 12 crunches.
2 sets of 12 sit up twisty things.
I'm so energetic right now.
I want to run.

Mmmm.
Bomb threat today.
chilled outside for an hour.
And came inside and chilled until ten.
Then they let us leave.
Awesome.
:)

I want to see how far my tennis can take me.
I know this sounds ridiculous and never gonna happen.
But I wanna go pro.
I wanna see how far my efforts can take me.
I wanna see how far my strength can.
I want to follow that little green ball for the rest of my life.

So today, was the last day of conference.
I was so pumped up,
And we lost to Nequa 6-0, 6-3.
After that we lost to Bartlett...
6-4, 4-6, 4-6.
I hope Wobonsie slaughtered them for third place.
Came back to school, had a group talk with Coach.
Went home.
And that was basically it.
I'm gonna go play tennis in a little.
Peace it.

asian

So my mom got a coupon or something from McDonalds.
She got me a happy meal and a salad.
So she's basically saying, "Be happy, but don't be fat."

Right now.
I hate everyone and everything.
Fucking emo kid.

Today we went to East Aurora, I played doubles with Allie.
We rocked them, 3-6, 6-2, 6-1.
It was amazing.
:D
We came home, stopped by Wendy's/Arby's and yeah.
Here I am.
My NHS essay is rocked and ready to go.
Hope I get in!

asian

So today Larkin invite.
Streamwood, St. Ed's, and Elgin were there.
I saw Misayo and Kristine.
:D
Anyways, I played the girl from St. Eds first.
Her doubles partner wasn't there so she was stuck playing two singles.  So both of us hit in the alleys a lot.  >.>;;;;
But I won 6-0, 6-1 :D
Easy peasy. 
/me is done being cocky.

Then I played this one asian girl from Streamwood.
She's a freshman.  =o
We had a good rally every now and then, but I won 6-1, 6-2

And then I played this girl from Elgin, and OMG HER FOREHANDS WERE CRAZY GOOD.
She holds it...well...I don't know the right name for it but yeah...
AMAZING.
I thought she would kill me.
But her forehands let up when we started playing.
So that was good for me.
We had the most amazingly long rallys that lasted FOREVER.
There was a point where we were stuck at deuce for fifteen minutes.
IT WAS HORRIBLE.
x.x
And I was running out of energy after the tiebreaker of the first set.
And so coach gave me some Powerade and then it started kicking in during the second set.
But in the end...
I WON.
\o/
7-6, 6-2

I was sooooo happy.
Everyone did so amazing, and Maya put up the biggest fight I have ever seen out of her.
It was amazing.
Although, in the end we got second place because Elgin lost three less games then us.
=/
But oh well, both our singles got FIRST PLACE.  =o
And both doubles got SECOND PLACE.
It was AMAZING.

And Aleah's dad got us TACO BELL.  It was the best ever.
I inhaled the nachos.
To the MAX!!!!!

Anyways, coach was talking and he said that we did amazing today.  :D
And he said I did good and that my playing is making him reconsider the lineup.
=o
Most amazing Saturday ever.

I'm planning to go shopping with Dally today, or go play tennis.
Most likely both.

asian

This is going to be my little talky talky after so long.
It's going to involve Richard, tennis, and burgers.
Basically just a shit load of randomness.

So Thursday, me and Dally went to the library to get some books and whatnot.
We came back and passed Wing Park, after we got a little gas we went back to Wing Park to see who was over there.
Of course, it was the asians.
So we stayed and talked and played a little tennis in sandals and barefeet and Richard pops out of nowhere and yes.
He told us to come back tomorrow.

Friday, I was afriad Dally wouldn't be able to come because she came home late and her dad was mad.
So I told Richard that I might not go because Dally wasn't going.  But he told me to go.  So...*shrug*
We told Selwyn to come along as well.
After school, we had practice then I went home, showered, and my dad told me to drop him off at NJ. Tech to get the truck.  So I drop him off and truck all the way over to Wing Park.
The asians were there agian, but Richard wasn't.  So I sat and watched everyone play.
Kirk didn't recgonize me at first.
:|
After a while Selwyn and Andy show up and we wait for a court to open, then Richard shows up and we wait a little more.
Finally a court opened up and we rallyed.
Richard popped my other racket's strings and he felt really really bad about it.  Haha, so he said he would string it.  We talked for a while and then played some more.
At 2130 the lights shut off after we were rallying.
We were all like, "SHIT!  WE FORGOT WHAT TIME IT WAS!" And so I had to turn on my headlights.
I was giving Selwyn a ride home and we started heading to my car when he said my light was broken.
Richard said, "You better fix that before you get pulled over some day."
So I ran up and whacked it and...IT WORKED!  Richard couldn't stop laughing.
Anyway, he said he would string my racket this weekend and his so we can play when he has his racket.  So I told him to call me and gave him my number and so on and so forth.
I went to drop Selwyn off and started heading back home and I almost got lost...;_;
And then I almost ran into a bush...
:|

Saturday, I slept for most of the day.
It was beastly.

Today I had to pick up my dad from work, then we went to Algonquin commons and shopped around.  I got a black shirt from Gap.
\o/
We stopped by a bar and grill place and got some REALLY REALLY good burgers.  They were like...the size of my face.
Came home, went to go pick up my dad's meds from Jewel, stopped by Wing Park just for the hell of it.
And now I'm ready to finish my face sized burger.

asian

I hung out with kevin tonight.
It was so much fun.
I would talk about it.
But I'm too tired.
I've never cried so much in one day before.

Tired.
So much tennis.
My sleeping schedule is still whack.
Ghey.

School is tomorrow.
When things get heavy with schoolwork.
I'm comitting myself to it 100%.
In my freetime I'll study Japanese by myself.
I need to do amazing this year.

My mom is letting me drive to tennis practice now.
I like having that little bit of freedom.
I can drive around with my dad's car whenever I want too.
But when Selena comes back then I can't use it anymore.
:|

My mom let me drive to tenni practice since she was gonna be late for work.
I saw Justin there.
Now I can't stop thinking about him.
Am I really that fickle?

Tennis started.
Need to get better.
I need to improve a hundredfold.
I need that singles spot.

I guess I don't make a big impression on people since no one really asks to hang out.
I've spent a lot of quility time with my computer.
And I think it's sick of me.
Fuck it all.

Loolking at cute Japanese clothes makes me sad becuase I can't order them.
;_;
I HATE BEING IN THIS FUCKING HOUSE

I hate myself.
I hate how stupid I am.
I hate how much I lack commitment.
I hate how I waste my life in front of the computer.
I hate it all.
I hate myself so much.
I hate how soft I am.
I hate how everything has turned out in my life.
I hate how I'm always one step below everyone.
I hate how I can't succed in anything.
I can't even look out for Selena.
She's always looking out after me.
I hate what I am.
